				<li id="16724439" class="cmnt-root" data="6" data-d="1656310740000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579682/Bolt-of-Gransax" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">27 Jun 2022 02:19</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16724439" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">the directions here on how to get it before killing godfrey the golden shade are fine, until you get on the roof of the gazebo, then it gets it wrong. if you follow these directions thinking to jump to the south west there is no ledge or anything to jump to from the gazebo. instead stand facing the body that you looted for a stonesword key, then turn a little to your right you&apos;ll see the ledge to jump to, its a little past south towards south east on the compass, I&apos;ve just been testing the jump and using the body that was holding the stonesword key as a marker has worked every time.  sprint forward then jump when you are just past the body&apos;s head you&apos;ll land perfectly exactly where you want to be. from there just keep hitting jump and pushing forward until you can climb onto the giant spear.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16724439" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16724439" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></s