				<li id="16720324" class="cmnt-root" data="1" data-d="1655785722000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579682/Bolt-of-Gransax" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">21 Jun 2022 00:28</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16720324" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">For the non-Godfrey route to get this, it&apos;s much easier to run to the Avenue Balcony Grace so you have a straight re-run to the Gazebo.<br/>From the East Capital Rampart go forward until the roofs on the right of the Flame Thrower Golem, jump on them and continue forwards until you see a carriage on the middle walkway that is the boss arena for the Erdtree Avatar, then turn right behind the Avatar to get to the Avenue Balcony Grace.<br/><br/>From there run back where you came and turn right towards the main gate stairs and take a left before them and towards a second flight of stairs where the mentioned broken railing to jump on the gazebo is on the left to a bigger gazebo in front of you.<br/><br/>Much safer and overall faster run if you die.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16720324" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16720324" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote